Dear Friends ! , this single verse is among the finest declarations of Vedānta's intellectual integrity. Mahārṣi Vasiṣṭha establishes that reason is not the destination, but it is an indispensable bridge. Mere logic cannot reveal Brahman, yet without purified reasoning the mind remains entangled in contradiction.
The progression of Sarga 183 is becoming beautifully clear:
Part One: A sincere doubt is raised.
Part Two: The dignity and necessity of sound reasoning are established.
Part Three: Mahārṣi Vasiṣṭha will begin unveiling how Consciousness itself resolves what the ordinary mind considers impossible.
This gradual unfolding is one of the literary and philosophical beauties of the Yoga Vāsiṣṭha. Hari Om Tat Sat. 🙏🌿
